If it comes from other EU countries, then poverty will move from one country to another; this capital may not come either, or then a Chinese, an Indian, a Brazilian, a Turkish, a Moroccan, an Egyptian or African will continue to work for a fraction of a European salary.
This also applies to all Latin America.
Liberal theory and the media claim, to be lamented, that the state cannot make capital investments in its own economy, that the led economy leads to an economic disaster.
Private capital strongly supports the idea that the State cannot intervene in the economy through regulatory interventions.
The question must then be asked whether private capital does not influence and, even today, does not, according to its own selfish interests, govern politics and by the same, the whole state.
The answer to this question is without a doubt yes.
Evidence of this is that there is a lobby that is practically all-powerful and present in all States.
