"I will not retire, I will die here because the volcano is my whole life," says Unainik, opening his mouth well, revealing several missing teeth.
The elder of his five children, aged 30, also works as a sulphur carrier.
Time passes, but the perpetual misery from generation to generation is one of the most difficult occupations in the world: the man-made mules of the Kawah ljen volcano.
